 races in an effort to allocate resources in a way that satisfies individual candidates, while simultaneously advancing broader party goals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPolitical campaigns -- United States -- History -- 21st century. 0aPolitical campaignszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aPolitical parties -- United States -- History -- 21st century. 0aPolitical partieszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 4aPolitics and Law : Electoral Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Parties. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438446097423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438446097/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles